The paper deals with extractive text summarization, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for sequence classification is a common technique in NLP, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG), which are also relevant sub-categories. The use of abstractive summaries and the CNN corpus suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with text, which is a common topic in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category.
